JOHANNESBURG - The family of late Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu has confirmed that his widow, Thembi, has died. She passed away in a Pretoria hospital on Thursday morning. A family member has confirmed that she was ill for some time. Her husband, Jackson, passed away early last year after he contracted COVID-19. Mthembu's cousin, Artwel Mthembu: "She was not well for the last couple of weeks. She lost her life in hospital. To open up the wounds, we lost Jackson last year."